    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/340</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Cork</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cork</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Queenstown</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1917-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Saxonian’s</hi> second boat picked up 17 hours after disaster.
                        <persName>James Weygand</persName>, native American, Hattboro, Montgomery
                    County, Pa., was wounded in foot and shoulder by shell which killed boatswain.
                    Ell wood Moore, native American, 1221 South Grand Avenue, St. Louis, was in same
                    boat. Shelling believed deliberate, killing boatswain, wounding four others. Am
                    mailing affidavits foregoing Americans and ship’s first and third officers.
                    Third American saved in boat afloat 68 hours, <persName>John
                        Steffinini</persName>, 2338 Filbert Street, San Francisco, native citizen.
                    This telegram sent also Ambassador, Consul General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
